[src:2016-united-states-presidential-election-in-colorado/1876-united-states-presidential-election-in-colorado] The **1876 United States presidential election in Colorado** took place on November 7, 1876, as part of the 1876 United States presidential election.
[src:2016-united-states-presidential-election-in-colorado/1876-united-states-presidential-election-in-colorado] The state legislature chose three representatives, or electors to the Electoral College, who voted for president and vice president, which would be the first and only time the state would do so.
[src:2016-united-states-presidential-election-in-colorado/1876-united-states-presidential-election-in-colorado] Colorado voted in its first ever presidential election, having become the 38th state on August 1 of that year.
[src:2016-united-states-presidential-election-in-colorado/1876-united-states-presidential-election-in-colorado] The state cast three electoral votes for the Republican candidate Rutherford B.
[src:2016-united-states-presidential-election-in-colorado/1876-united-states-presidential-election-in-colorado] This proved to be decisive as Hayes would win the electoral vote by a margin of one vote.
[src:2016-united-states-presidential-election-in-colorado/1876-united-states-presidential-election-in-colorado] Had Colorado not been a state in time for the 1876 election, Hayes would have lost the 1876 election to Democratic candidate Samuel J.
[src:2016-united-states-presidential-election-in-colorado/1876-united-states-senate-elections-in-colorado] The **1876–77 United States Senate elections** were held on various dates in various states, coinciding with Rutherford B.
[src:2016-united-states-presidential-election-in-colorado/1876-united-states-senate-elections-in-colorado] Senate elections were prior to the ratification of the Seventeenth Amendment in 1913, senators were chosen by state legislatures.
[src:2016-united-states-presidential-election-in-colorado/1876-united-states-senate-elections-in-colorado] Senators were elected over a wide range of time throughout 1876 and 1877, and a seat may have been filled months late or remained vacant due to legislative deadlock.
[src:2016-united-states-presidential-election-in-colorado/1876-united-states-senate-elections-in-colorado] In these elections, terms were up for the senators in Class 2.
[src:2016-united-states-presidential-election-in-colorado/1876-united-states-senate-elections-in-colorado] Although the Republican Party maintained their Senate majority, the Democratic Party gained five seats.
[src:2016-united-states-presidential-election-in-colorado/1876-united-states-senate-elections-in-colorado] After the November 15, 1876 elections in the new state of Colorado.
